(37, '2013-01-07 08:31:36', '2013-09-23 19:02:28', 2, '2D Mulitplayer Test Engine', '<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.animation.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.keyboard.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.map.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.network.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.player.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.spriteSheet.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.tile.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.timer.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/engine.viewport.js"></script>\r\n<script type="application/javascript" src="javascript/tileEngine3/main.js"></script>\r\n\r\n<p>This is my multiplayer 2D side-scrolling tile engine. The server not currently running. I''m currently refactoring node.js websockets and the network protocol. The 2D game engine should still function normally though.</p>\r\n\r\n<style type="text/css">\r\n	canvas#canvas {\r\n		border: 1px dotted #888;\r\n	}\r\n	div#chatBox {\r\n		position: absolute;\r\n		/* left: 24px; */\r\n		font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\r\n		font-size: 10px;\r\n		color: #FFF;\r\n		background-color: rgba(32,64,128,0.15);\r\n		width: 240px;\r\n		height: 120px;\r\n		overflow-x: hidden;\r\n		overflow-y: hidden;\r\n	}\r\n	input#chatInput {\r\n		position: absolute;\r\n		/* left: 24px; */\r\n		/* top: 190px; */\r\n		background: transparent;\r\n		font-family: Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif;\r\n		font-size: 10px;\r\n		color: #FFF;\r\n		border: none;\r\n		width: 240px;\r\n	}\r\n	div#console {\r\n		border: 1px dotted #888;\r\n		width: 640px;\r\n		height: 150px;\r\n		overflow-x: hidden;\r\n		overflow-y: auto;\r\n	}\r\n</style>\r\n\r\n<div id="container">\r\n<div id="chatBox"></div>\r\n<input type="text" id="chatInput" onkeypress="engine.chat(event, this)"/>\r\n<canvas id="canvas" width="640" height="480"><p>HTML5 Canvas not supported.</p></canvas>\r\n</div>\r\n<br/>\r\n<div id="console"></div>\r\n<br/>', 'HTML5, Canvas, Javascript, Demo, Game, Mulitplayer', 'images\\2dmulti.png'),
(38, '2013-02-05 15:39:51', '2013-02-05 20:17:50', 4, 'Vehicles', '<br/>\r\n<img class="preview" src="imageResize.php?f=images/impound.jpg&w=160&h=160"/>\r\n<p>This is one of my MTA 1.3 resources. It came from a folder marked "[Project]". I''ll quickly scan over it & try to explain it a bit, but I haven''t seen this code in almost a year.</p>\r\n<p>When this is started it should load a list of vehicles from the SQL table and create them with all attributes that are stored in the DB (position, rotation, color, paintjob, upgrades, & handling).  Before the resource is stopped it saves a copy of all live vehicles (and their attributes) to the DB. Users in the ACL group "PublicAccess" can use the commands "/park" & "/impound". You can create and manage ACL groups through the admin panel resource. Parking a vehicle sets it''s respawn position. Impounding a vehicle permanently removes it from the world.</p>\r\n<p>There are a few other simple client side functions like "/vBlips" that will show/hide blips on the radar for all vehicles. It looks like vehicles.xml is just a .map file from an older version of this resource.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/vehicles/vehicles_client.lua">View: vehicles_client.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/vehicles/vehicles_server.lua">View: vehicles_server.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/vehicles/vehicles.xml">View: vehicles.xml</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/vehicles/meta.xml">View: meta.xml</a>\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<a href="/mta/vehicles.zip">Download: vehicles.zip</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<script type="text/javascript">\r\n$(document).ready(function() {\r\n  $(".viewSource").fancybox({\r\n    padding : 0,\r\n    width: ''70%'',\r\n    height: ''70%'',\r\n    maxWidth: 800,\r\n    maxHeight: 600,\r\n    autoSize	: false,\r\n    fitToView: false,\r\n    closeClick: false,\r\n    preload: false,\r\n    type: ''iframe'',\r\n    openEffect: ''elastic'',\r\n    closeEffect: ''elastic''\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n</script>', 'Lua, MTA resource', 'images\\impound.jpg'),
(39, '2013-02-05 15:40:29', '2013-02-05 20:18:02', 4, 'Warp', '<br/>\r\n<img class="preview" src="imageResize.php?f=images/warp.jpg&w=160&h=160"/>\r\n<p>This is my MTA 1.3 interior warping resource. It is many times faster/smoother than the default "Interiors" resource that''s included with MTA. Most of the code is on the client-side. It allows players to RUN though doors and can be simply modified to allow vehicles to drive through warps.</p>\r\n<p>Warp elements are saved in the "warp.xml" map file. Each warp needs a position (x,y,z), a rotation (in degrees) to rotate player that gets warped here, an interior, dimension, an "id", and a "to" (a different warp id) that this warp will go to. Each warp can be hidden (no marker displayed) by adding <code>hidden="true"</code>. There is also an optional "name" attribute that will works together with my <a href="/index.php?action=view&page=41">Text3D</a> resource.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/warp/warp_client.lua">View: warp_client.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/warp/warp_server.lua">View: warp_server.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/warp/warp.xml">View: warp.xml</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/warp/meta.xml">View: meta.xml</a>\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<a href="/mta/warp.zip">Download: warp.zip</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<script type="text/javascript">\r\n$(document).ready(function() {\r\n  $(".viewSource").fancybox({\r\n    padding : 0,\r\n    width: ''70%'',\r\n    height: ''70%'',\r\n    maxWidth: 800,\r\n    maxHeight: 600,\r\n    autoSize	: false,\r\n    fitToView: false,\r\n    closeClick: false,\r\n    preload: false,\r\n    type: ''iframe'',\r\n    openEffect: ''elastic'',\r\n    closeEffect: ''elastic''\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n</script>', 'Lua, MTA resource', 'images\\warp.jpg'),
(40, '2013-02-05 16:23:13', '2013-02-05 20:18:27', 4, 'Recoil', '<img class="preview" src="imageResize.php?f=images/recoil.jpg&w=160&h=160"/>\r\n<p>This is a short script from my MTA [Project] folder. It triggers a silent explosion 10 units beneath your player onClientPlayerWeaponFire which shakes the camera. Client side only, MTA 1.3\r\n</p>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<p>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/recoil/recoil_client.lua">View: recoil_client.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/recoil/meta.xml">View: meta.xml</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a href="/mta/recoil.zip">Download: recoil.zip</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<script type="text/javascript">\r\n$(document).ready(function() {\r\n  $(".viewSource").fancybox({\r\n    padding : 0,\r\n    width: ''70%'',\r\n    height: ''70%'',\r\n    maxWidth: 800,\r\n    maxHeight: 600,\r\n    autoSize	: false,\r\n    fitToView: false,\r\n    closeClick: false,\r\n    preload: false,\r\n    type: ''iframe'',\r\n    openEffect: ''elastic'',\r\n    closeEffect: ''elastic''\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n</script>', 'Lua, MTA resource', 'images\\recoil.jpg'),
(41, '2013-02-05 19:43:45', '2013-02-05 20:18:14', 4, 'Text3D', '<br/>\r\n<img class="preview" src="imageResize.php?f=images/text3d.jpg&w=160&h=160"/>\r\n<p>Another resource from my MTA 1.3 [Project]. It creates custom Text3D elements using dxDrawText. There are a few examples in the text3d.xml map file. Each text3D element needs a position (x,y,z), interior, dimension, text, r,g,b, size, and font. If the <a href="/index.php?action=view&page=39">Warp</a> resource is running "onClientResourceStart" then this will automatically create new text3D elements for each warp element that has a "name" attribute.\r\n</p>\r\n<br/>\r\n<p>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/text3d/text3d_client.lua">View: text3d_client.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/text3d/text3d_server.lua">View: text3d_server.lua</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/text3d/text3d.xml">View: text3d.xml</a>\r\n<br/>\r\n<a class="viewSource fancybox.ajax" href="viewSource.php?file=/mta/text3d/meta.xml">View: meta.xml</a>\r\n<br/><br/>\r\n<a href="/mta/text3d.zip">Download: text3d.zip</a>\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<script type="text/javascript">\r\n$(document).ready(function() {\r\n  $(".viewSource").fancybox({\r\n    padding : 0,\r\n    width: ''70%'',\r\n    height: ''70%'',\r\n    maxWidth: 800,\r\n    maxHeight: 600,\r\n    autoSize	: false,\r\n    fitToView: false,\r\n    closeClick: false,\r\n    preload: false,\r\n    type: ''iframe'',\r\n    openEffect: ''elastic'',\r\n    closeEffect: ''elastic''\r\n  });\r\n});\r\n</script>', 'Lua, MTA resource', 'images\\text3d.jpg');

